        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 14 at 12:22AM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 1222 AM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 4
miles northwest of Mocksville, moving east at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Mocksville, Bermuda Run, Sheffield, Fork Church, Farmington, and
Advance.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
